      <abstract>
        <p>Six people contract hepatitis after eating at McGowan's Pizzaland in Monroe, Conn, where employee fell ill with hepatitis in November (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Six people who ate at a pizza restaurant in Monroe have contracted hepatitis A, state health officials said yesterday. In November, an employee of the restaurant, McGowan's Pizzaland, fell ill with the disease, and that same month, six people who dined there also contracted the disease. The source of the outbreak is not known. The restaurant is closed and will reopen after an inspection by health officials.</p>
        <p>Stacey Stowe (NYT)</p>
      </block>
